        <div class="highlight">
            <strong>Summary:</strong> We respect your privacy. Your API keys are stored locally on your device. We don't
            collect, store, or sell your personal data or designs.
        </div>

        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Printify Automation ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy
            explains how we handle information when you use our Chrome extension.</p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>API Keys:</strong> Printify, Gemini, and OpenAI API keys you enter are stored locally in your
                browser using Chrome's storage API. These keys never leave your device except when making API calls to
                the respective services.</li>
            <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> If you create an account, we store your email address and
                subscription status.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Information We Don't Collect</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>We do NOT collect or store your design images</li>
            <li>We do NOT track your browsing history</li>
            <li>We do NOT sell any data to third parties</li>
            <li>We do NOT use cookies for advertising</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.3 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Usage Statistics:</strong> Basic usage counts (products created) for subscription limits</li>
            <li><strong>Error Logs:</strong> Anonymous error reports to improve the extension</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide and maintain the extension functionality</li>
            <li>Track subscription usage limits</li>
            <li>Improve our services and fix bugs</li>
            <li>Communicate important updates</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Data Storage and Security</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Local Storage</h3>
        <p>Your API keys and preferences are stored locally using Chrome's <code>chrome.storage.local</code> API. This
            data remains on your device and is not transmitted to our servers.</p>

        <h3>4.2 Server Storage</h3>
        <p>If you create an account, the following is stored on our secure servers:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Email address (for account identification)</li>
            <li>Hashed password (we never store plain text passwords)</li>
            <li>Subscription plan and usage statistics</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.3 Security Measures</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>All data transmission uses HTTPS encryption</li>
            <li>Passwords are hashed using industry-standard algorithms</li>
            <li>API keys are never logged or stored on our servers</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>Our extension interacts with the following third-party services:</p>

        <h3>5.1 Printify</h3>
        <p>We use the Printify API to create products. Your designs and product data are sent directly to Printify.
            Please review <a href="https://printify.com/privacy-policy/" target="_blank">Printify's Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>5.2 Google Gemini / OpenAI</h3>
        <p>If you use AI content generation, your text prompts are sent to Google or OpenAI. Review their respective
            privacy policies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank">OpenAI Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your data</li>
            <li><strong>Correction:</strong> Update inaccurate information</li>
            <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> Delete your account and associated data</li>
            <li><strong>Export:</strong> Export your data in a portable format</li>
        </ul>
        <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:ken.d150212@gmail.com">ken.d150212@gmail.com</a>.</p>

        <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local Data:</strong> Stored until you uninstall the extension or clear browser data</li>
            <li><strong>Account Data:</strong> Retained while your account is active; deleted within 30 days of account
                closure</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Logs:</strong> Retained for 90 days for subscription tracking</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our service is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under
            13. If you believe we have collected such information, please contact us immediately.</p>

        <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Posting the new policy on this page</li>
            <li>Updating the "Last updated" date</li>
            <li>Sending an email notification for material changes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:ken.d150212@gmail.com">ken.d150212@gmail.com</a></li>
        </ul>
